observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the Municipal Mayor agreed to:
a. require the Inventory Committee to complete the conduct of the physical count of all Inventories and PPE of the Municipality and  undertake all other procedures  prescribed under COA Circular 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020;

b. instruct the GSO Designate and the Municipal Accountant to reconcile their records after the physical count and effect the necessary adjustments, if any;

c. require the GSO Designate to submit to the Auditor the semestral RPCI not later than July 31 and January 31 of each year for the first and second semesters, respectively;

d. require the GSO Designate to submit to the Auditor the RPCPPE as of December 31 not later than January 31 of the ensuing year, and

e.  instruct the GSO Designate to undertake proper disposal of unserviceable properties, if any.

In order to correct the aforementioned deficiencies, we recommended and the Municipal Mayor agreed to:

instruct all the heads of offices to fill out all the data in the PR and indicate the exact unit of measure and complete specifications of items being requested to be purchased and avoid indicating the brand name except for replacement of parts;

instruct the GSO Designate to see to it that all the data in the RFQ/Canvass Paper are completely filled out and that the exact unit of measure and complete specifications of items being canvassed are indicated therein except the brand name unless the items are replacements of parts;

instruct the GSO Designate to require the bidders to indicate in the RFQ/Bill of Quantities the brand name of items they are quoting which shall be  incorporated in the PO;

instruct the GSO Designate to see to it that all data in the PO are completely filled out and the exact unit of measure and complete specifications of items being ordered are indicated therein including the brand name of the items as indicated by the winning bidder in the RFQ/Canvass Paper/Bill of Quantities;

instruct the   Municipal Accountant and the GSO Designate   who sign the inspection and acceptance portions of the AIR respectively that such document is properly filled out and the exact unit of measure and complete specifications of items accepted and inspected including the brand name of the items be indicated therein;

require the GSO Designate to attach History of Repair  using the prescribed format indicating among others the  plate number and date of acquisition of the vehicle being repaired and  the dates and complete details of   all previous repairs undertaken including the current repair;

instruct the Municipal Treasurer to submit the original copy official receipts of remittances to GSIS in the total amount of ₱8,039,935.76 and henceforth, attach  said document to the disbursement voucher;

require the Municipal Accountant to issue a certification that the previous cash advance of the payee has been liquidated before processing payment for another cash advance;

require the Municipal Accountant to see to it that cash advances for payroll are supported with payroll duly signed by the signatories indicated in Boxes A to D therein without the signatures of the payees, as basis of the amount to be cash advanced.  

Likewise, see to it that cash advances for specific purpose/time bound undertaking be supported with breakdown of estimated expenditures, and

require the head of office in charge of the activity for which meals and/or snacks shall be served to participants or visitors to see to it that these are supported with duly accomplished Attendance Sheet indicating the date and title of the activity, the name and signatures of participants and pictures taken showing that the participants are taking their meals/snacks;

instruct the Municipal Health Officer and the Municipal Accountant that henceforth, purchases of medicines be supported with Certificate of Product Registration, Certificate of Good Manufacturing Practice from FDA, Batch Release Certificate from FDA and Certification from the manufacturer that the supplier is an authorized distributor to ensure the safeness and effectives of the items purchased; and

require the head of office in charge of the distribution of the rambutan seedlings costing ₱292,824.99 to submit duly accomplished List of Recipients indicating among others the date of distribution, the name and address of the recipients, the quantity and specifications of the items distributed and the signatures of the recipients.  

Henceforth, see to it that goods distributed to beneficiaries are supported with duly accomplished List of Recipients and pictures during distribution as ready references that distribution took place.

In order to present the correct balances of Inventories and PPE accounts in the financial statements, we reiterated our previous recommendations that the Municipal Mayor:

require the Inventory Committee to complete the conduct of the physical count of all Inventories and PPE of the Municipality and avail of the procedures of One-Time Cleansing of PPE balances prescribed under COA Circular 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020;

instruct the GSO Designate and the Municipal Accountant to reconcile their records after the physical count and effect the necessary adjustments, if any;

require the GSO Designate to submit to the Auditor the semestral RPCI not later than July 31 and January 31 of each year for the first and second semesters, respectively;

require the GSO Designate to submit to the Auditor the RPCPPE as of December 31 not later than January 31 of the ensuing year, and

instruct the GSO Designate to undertake proper disposal of unserviceable properties, if any.

In order to correct the aforementioned deficiencies, we recommended and the Municipal Mayor agreed that henceforth:

require the Municipal Treasurer to prepare a schedule of all delinquent taxpayers as of year-end;

instruct the Municipal Treasurer and the Municipal Accountant to reconcile their records on RPT and SET Receivables and effect the necessary adjustments in order to reflect the correct balances of these accounts together with the Deferred RPT and SET Income in the financial statements;

require the Municipal Accountant to see to it that the balances of these accounts are duly supported with schedules as required under Section 58 of PD 1445.

